{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Only files changed in the pull request are analyzed — unchanged files are not scanned.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure mode is at the handoff between PR-change discovery and file-analysis scheduling. A pure unit test of selector logic can miss wiring bugs where the analyzer still receives unchanged paths. System was considered, but rejected because the behavior text is about selection correctness (\"Only files changed... unchanged files are not scanned\"), not OS/network/subprocess variability.","test_description":"Wire PR-file-list provider + analysis orchestrator + analyzer stub in-process; feed a mixed repo fixture where only a subset is marked changed; assert analyzer is invoked only for changed files and never for unchanged files.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.6,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Findings are grouped by severity (error, warning, info) in the posted PR comment.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Real risk is contract mismatch between rule output schema, grouping logic, and comment-render payload. Unit tests on grouping alone can miss end-to-end formatting/assembly defects. System was considered, but rejected because behavior text targets grouping in comment content, not real GitHub API transport behavior.","test_description":"Run parser/aggregator/comment-render modules together with deterministic findings across severities; verify final comment body contains correctly separated error/warning/info sections and each finding appears in the expected group.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.35,"Integration":0.55,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"A pull request that touches 200 files completes analysis within the 10-minute Actions timeout.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"This is an environment-dependent performance/timeout requirement tied to GitHub Actions runtime limits. In-process mocks hide real wall-clock behavior, subprocess overhead, and CI resource constraints. Higher levels are disqualified because no AI/ML output or multi-agent chain is involved.","test_description":"Execute the actual lint step in CI (or a faithfully equivalent runner) against a generated 200-file PR-sized fixture, measure end-to-end wall-clock time, and fail if total duration exceeds 10 minutes.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.82,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"When the linter process crashes on a malformed file, the remaining files are still analyzed and results posted.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Behavior explicitly references a crashing linter process, so correctness depends on real subprocess failure handling and continuation semantics. Mocking process execution can always pass and miss crash/exit-signal edge cases. Agentic/Workflow are disqualified because no model output dependency or multi-agent sequence is described.","test_description":"Run orchestrator against a fixture containing one crash-inducing malformed file plus valid files, invoke real linter subprocess, assert pipeline records the crash, continues analyzing remaining files, and emits a final consolidated PR-comment payload.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.2,"System":0.73,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Duplicate findings on the same line from overlapping rules are deduplicated in the output.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Although dedup can be algorithmic, real failure often appears when outputs from multiple rule modules are merged (key-shape/source mismatch). Integration best matches this boundary. System was considered, but rejected because behavior text focuses on output dedup semantics, not OS/network/subprocess effects.","test_description":"Feed orchestrator with findings emitted from two overlapping rules against the same file/line and same semantic issue; run merge + dedup + output formatting path and assert exactly one output entry is produced per unique issue location/signature.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.4,"Integration":0.5,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}}]}
